    <bioghist>Arno Whitbread, from Detroit, served with the 101st Airborne Infantry Division during World War II as a member of the 327th Glider Infantry Regiment. Whitbread landed in Normandy by glider on June 7, 1944.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Scrapbook of Detroit newspaper coverage of the D-Day invasion and subsequent progress with an emphasis on airborne operations. Includes postcards and ephemera from Berchtesgaden where Whitbread was stationed at the end of the war.</scopecontent>
